 are taught, often without question. Pushing the boundaries of education theory, research, and practice, this book will be of particular interest to feminist, adult, and teacher educators and to scholars and students of education, the military, and women’s and gender studies. Contributors: Mark Anthony Castrodale, Gillian L. Fournier, Andrew Haddow, Cindy L. Hanson, Laura Lane, Jamie Magnusson, Robert C. Mizzi, Shahrzad Mojab, Snežana Ratković, Roger Saul, Nancy Taber.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducational sociologyzCanada. 0aMilitarismxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aSex rolezCanada. 7aHISTORY / Military / Canada.2bisacsh  aGender Studies/Education/Military Studies.1 aCastrodale, Mark Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFournier, Gillian L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGouthro, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddow, Andrew Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddow, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanson, Cindy L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanson, Cindy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLane, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagnusson, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMizzi, Robert C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMojab, Shahrzad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRatkovic, Snežana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRatković, Snežana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaul, Roger, econtributor.4ct